            "title": "Coherent-mode representations in optics",
            "abstract": [
                "3. Coherent-Mode Representation of Propagation-Invariant Fields -- Propagation-Invariant Fields -- Coherent-Mode Structure of the Propagation-Invariant Field -- Special Classes of Propagation-Invariant Fields -- Generation of Propagation-Invariant Fields -- Physical Simulation",
                "This book provides you with a single source of information on the problem of coherent-mode representations in optics, including new perspectives on its potential applications. In particular, the \"light string\" and the \"light capillary\" beams may be advantageously used in communications, measurements, laser microtechnology, and microsurgery; application of the fast algorithm for bilinear transforms can significantly reduce the computer effort needed to simulate optical systems with partially coherent illumination",
                "1. Coherent-Mode Representation of Optical Fields and Sources -- Foundations of the Coherence Theory in the Space-Frequency Domain -- Coherent-Mode Structure of the Field -- Ensemble Representation of the Cross-Spectral Density Function -- Effective Number of Coherent Modes -- Coherent-Mode Representations of Some Model Sources",
                "4. Coherent-Mode Representations in Radiometry -- Generalized Radiant Flux -- Coherent-Mode Representation of Radiometric Quantities -- Free-Space Propagation of Modal Radiance -- Modal Radiometry of Gaussian Schell-Model Source",
                "2. Coherent-Mode Representation of Optical Systems -- Bilinear Systems in Optics -- Coherent-Mode Representations of a Bilinear System -- Fast Algorithm for Bilinear Transforms in Optics -- Numerical Simulation",
                "5. Alternative Coherent-Mode Representation of a Planar Source -- Alternative Source and its Coherent-Mode Structure -- Choice of the Alternative Modal Basis -- Numerical Simulation"
